__label__booksthe time machine about the author born in bromley in kent england herbert george h g wells 1866 1946 has been called the father of science fiction his most notable works include the war of the worlds 1897 the time machine 1895 the invisible man 1897 and the island of doctor moreau 1896 wells also wrote on topics related to history and social commentary and was involved in politics for much of his life novels like kipps and the history of mr polly which describe lower middle class life led to the suggestion that he was a worthy successor to charles dickens wells died in london in august 1946 after living through two world wars the war of the worlds has been both popular having never gone out of print and influential spawning half a dozen feature films radio dramas a record album various comic book adaptations a television series and sequels or parallel stories by other authors
