__label__booksfrom puritanism to postmodernism a history of american literature about the author malcolm bradbury was an english author critic and academician he was the emeritus professor of american studies at the university of east anglia and has written books like the history man and stepping westward he was shortlisted for the booker prize for rates of exchange in 1991 the author became a commander of the british empire he was made a knight bachelor in 2000 in the new year honors he passed away the same year richard ruland is a professor at the department of english in washington university st louis he has written america in modern european literature and the rediscovery of american literature his research interests lie in literary history and cultural nationalism
