__label__booksdance dance dance review if raymond chandler had lived long enough to see blade runner he might have written something like dance dance dance observer an entertaining mix of modern sci fi nail biting suspense and ancient myth a sometimes funny sometimes sinister mystery spoof but like all good postmodern fiction it also aims at contemporary human concerns philosophical as well as literary chicago tribune an entertaining adventure that takes us to the frozen north of japan to hawaii and to the dark damp corners of the imagination reading dance dance dance is a bit like being taken blindfold on a joy ride independent mr murakami writes metaphysical far easterns with a western beat there are echoes of raymond chandler john irving and raymond carver but mr murakami's mysterious plots and original characters are very much his own creation new york times brilliantly combines elements of the surreal film noir and existentialist enquiry sunday times 				 	 					 book description an assault on the senses part murder mystery part metaphysical speculation a fable for our times as catchy as a rock song blasting from the window of a sports car 				 	 					 see all product description
