__label__booksconsciousness and the brain deciphering how the brain codes our thoughts review this book's spunky writing and popular topic should have made transforming it into an appealing audio an easy proposition but david drummond's repetitive tonal patterns give the production a flat quality that falls short of making this title the joyous exploration of the mind that the publisher claims it to be drummond's phrasing is always clear but he repeats the same pitch sequences again and again however the author's boyish enthusiasm for this kind of psychological inquiry saves the production and helps it deliver a stirring look at how today's scientists are parsing the experience of being conscious t w 				 	 					 about the author stanislas dehaene is the director of the cognitive neuroimaging unit in saclay france and the author of reading in the brain david drummond has made his living as an actor for over twenty five years and he received an audiofile earphones award for his first audiobook love 'em or lose 'em
